HEADWORD: Scholiast
<hw>Scho"li*ast</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/, fr. <?/
a scholium: cf. F. <ets>scoliate</ets>. See <er>Scholium</er>.]</ety>
<def>A maker of scholia; a commentator or annotator.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>No . . . quotations from Talmudists and <qex>scholiasts</qex> . .
. ever marred the effect of his grave temperate discourses.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scholiastic</ent>⟦br⟧
